responses.FT_EPS_S7 : Points forts de cet enseigne: The fact that we get to take some stress off during sports is non-negotiable. It provides an environment to interact with our colleagues and to showcase our talent. It also gives us  time to exercise our bodies which is good for the health.
responses.FT_FL2_S7 : Points forts de cet enseigne: I am english speaking, so I know the basics. But it gives opportunity to french speaking students to improve their english if they want to be more markatable in the engineering field. Furthermore, we get to learn the correct way of expressing ourselves in english professionally.
responses.FT_FLE_S7 : Points forts de cet enseigne: Everything I need to improve my french language level. The professor(s) are very kind and understanding and they push us to improve. The games we play at the end of each class facilitate quicker learning. Also this is the only subject with soutien, a very big strength.
responses.FT_ALGPR_S7 : Points forts de cet enseig: Even when our level of coding is still elementary, the professor is willing to go an extra mile. The course also helps us understand the power of C++, although we do not have time to explore everything.
responses.FT_OFM_S7 : Points forts de cet enseigne: This course is very practical in the industry when it comes to designs and models.
responses.FT_FINEL_S7 : Points forts de cet enseig: Very applicable in the engineering industry. Professor is kind.
responses.FT_MATH1_S7 : Points forts de cet enseig: Not sure. Was too abstract 80% of the time. Math level taught may be a bit too advanced. Maybe the students need a preparation course before. However, the course can be helpful for PhD pursuers or those interested in numerical mathematics as a major. Engineering knowledge can simply apply without knowing every tiny molecule of how the formular was developed or how the software was built. Just my opinion
responses.FT_SNS_S7 : Points forts de cet enseigne: Introduces a new field of engineering application.
responses.FT_ENERG_S7 : Points forts de cet enseig: Deeper understanding on the basic principals of Energy and thermodynamics which is applicable in various engineering fields.
responses.FT_ROBOT_S7 : Points forts de cet enseig: New knowledge for some of us. Never studied robotics before until i reached Centrale Nantes
responses.FT_EPS_S7 : Points faibles de cet enseig: I wish the sports professor would give us the plan for our sports class for the semester. For example, there are some games we want to play to show our talents and teach others but we are not sure if it is on the program or not. Or if we are allowed to suggest to be added to the program.
responses.FT_FL2_S7 : Points faibles de cet enseig: Need for more grammar practice. Anything to help in improving the structures of our English. Be it spoken or written.
responses.FT_FLE_S7 : Points faibles de cet enseig: I dont see any weak points
responses.FT_ALGPR_S7 : Points faibles de cet ense: The principles taught in class different from what was questioned in the exam. Normally, we should be able to adapt, but adapting the knowledge and the questions is rather difficult. Not all students have coding background. This should be taken into consideration. I learnt much more from the TP projects, than from preparing for the exam. I wish to have only TP projects through out. Like that it makes more sense.
responses.FT_OFM_S7 : Points faibles de cet enseig: Unrelated CM content to TP content. TP was very good, but the guiding CM was no where to be found. The teacher is available to assist, but without the basic knowledge, it is difficult
responses.FT_FINEL_S7 : Points faibles de cet ense: Lack of feedback on progress of things like TP1 feedback to make sure we improve in subsequent TPs. Knowledge not very complicated to understand. But feedback is required.
responses.FT_MATH1_S7 : Points faibles de cet ense: The maths level was tooooooooooo advanced. I speak for all those with me and before me. If a certain level of maths is required for fast track, then it should be communicated clearly. maybe an assessment on one's math level before being admitted into the program. Another mistake, is that international students have different maths background from the french students. The course therefore MUST be adapted to this. Or give the new international students some sort of preparation course before doing this Maths1.
responses.FT_SNS_S7 : Points faibles de cet enseig: Teacher tooo boring. Course abit abstract. It is applicable, but understanding the concepts is hard. Not everyone has interest, so it is hard to follow when you know you may never really use it in the future.
responses.FT_CIVEN_S7 : Points faibles de cet ense: It is good for introductory knowledge. For someone who did Civil Engineering in the past, it is less challenging.
responses.FT_ROBOT_S7 : Points faibles de cet ense: The assumption that all students should know certain complex concepts. When actually they do not know. How is a student able to communicate this without feeling like a failure. Robotics is not everywhere, so some people have never studied this.
responses.FT_EPS_S7 : Propositions pour am\u00e9li: To see the sports outline for the semester. Is it possible for the students to suggest what sports to play?
responses.FT_FL2_S7 : Propositions pour am\u00e9li: More individual tasks to help in assessing and improving one's level
responses.FT_FLE_S7 : Propositions pour am\u00e9li: So far so good for me
responses.FT_ALGPR_S7 : Propositions pour am\u00e9: No exam. More practical application. Assessments done, and feedback returned each time.
responses.FT_OFM_S7 : Propositions pour am\u00e9li: Relate the lectures to the projects to be done.
responses.FT_MATH1_S7 : Propositions pour am\u00e9: Professor not assume the maths level for all students. Course to be less abstract, more understandable and applicable to actual engineering situations. Please make the course less hard.
responses.FT_SNS_S7 : Propositions pour am\u00e9li: Make new concepts more understandable to students. Not assume we should know things, when we actually do not know. It limits student-teacher interaction because the tudent is scared to ask, to avoid looking like a failure. Teacher needs to be more approachable and know that we are in the class because we actually do not know but are willing to learn. If we knew that stuff, we would definitely not be in the class.
responses.FT_CIVEN_S7 : Propositions pour am\u00e9: Need for more structural engineering design concepts as opposed to just basic lab work.
responses.FT_ROBOT_S7 : Propositions pour am\u00e9: Avoid assuming that students should already know these hard complex concepts. Sometimes we dont know but we learn fast. The biggest hinderance to a student is making them feel like a failure. If all teachers in general could avoid assuming, then students would be more interactive. Students are quiet in class because they are afraid of saying the wrong thing, also because they do not know. It is new knowledge.

responses.FT_ALGPR_S7 : Points forts de cet enseig: accompagnement et rythme progressif dans la realisation du projet à rendre
responses.FT_OFM_S7 : Points forts de cet enseigne: Avoir pris du temps de bien progresser sur matlab pou en suite insérer et enforcer les nouvelles fonctions spécifiques à l'OFM
responses.FT_FINEL_S7 : Points forts de cet enseig: TP sur ansys pour developper son apprentissage du logiciel
responses.FT_MATH1_S7 : Points forts de cet enseig: les tutoriels pour la compréhension des nouvelles notions
responses.FT_SNS_S7 : Points forts de cet enseigne: pouvoir se reporter au livre pour toutes les parties du cours
responses.FT_CIVEN_S7 : Points forts de cet enseig: l'apprentissage très pratique pour ouvrir vers la théorie et les lois
responses.FT_ENERG_S7 : Points forts de cet enseig: le mode d'enseignement avec le livre complété progressivement
responses.FT_ROBOT_S7 : Points forts de cet enseig: l'engagement du professeur et la patience de réexpliquer plusieurs fois/ simplifier son explication quand tout le monde ne comprend pas

responses.FT_MATH1_S7 : Points faibles de cet ense: le coté abstrait et très conceptuel des maths 'à la française' - focalisés sur de la démonstration plus que de l'application
responses.FT_SNS_S7 : Points faibles de cet enseig: rythme un peu lent en cours sur les premiers cours
responses.FT_CIVEN_S7 : Points faibles de cet ense: avoir les séances TP et devoir les rendre les veilles/memes jours ou lendemains des partiels
responses.FT_ENERG_S7 : Points faibles de cet ense: le fait que pour chaque exercice il faille avoir toutes les questions précédentes bonnes et assurées pour progresser dans l'exercice.
